{
  "text": "Within the realm of this work, overheads on performance and tightened security should become more balanced or tunable by a \"dial\". This may also include the exploitation of average-case execution time in statistical sanity checks or probabilistic timing analysis-based systems or parametric models [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . More gradual warning systems might provide several steps of reduced functionality while raising the bar for intrusions if threats are detected, similar to the Simplex approach for reliability [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] .",
